### Expected behavior
The `AdaptivePoolingAllocator.CENTRAL_QUEUE_CAPACITY` and `AdaptivePoolingAllocator.MAGAZINE_BUFFER_QUEUE_CAPACITY` MUST NOT less than 2, otherwise it will rise an exception when initialize the `AdaptivePoolingAllocator` instance.

We should set them to 2 if less than 2 by using `Math.max(...)`:
```
    private static final int CENTRAL_QUEUE_CAPACITY = Math.max(2,
            SystemPropertyUtil.getInt(
            "io.netty.allocator.centralQueueCapacity", NettyRuntime.availableProcessors()));

    private static final int MAGAZINE_BUFFER_QUEUE_CAPACITY = Math.max(2,
            SystemPropertyUtil.getInt("io.netty.allocator.magazineBufferQueueCapacity", 1024));
```
or we fail-fast in the class load stage:
```
static {
        if (CENTRAL_QUEUE_CAPACITY < 2) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("CENTRAL_QUEUE_CAPACITY: " + CENTRAL_QUEUE_CAPACITY
                    + " (expected: >= " + 2 + ')');
        }
        if (MAGAZINE_BUFFER_QUEUE_CAPACITY < 2) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("MAGAZINE_BUFFER_QUEUE_CAPACITY: " + MAGAZINE_BUFFER_QUEUE_CAPACITY
                    + " (expected: >= " + 2 + ')');
        }
    }
```

### Actual behavior
https://github.com/netty/netty/blob/a0e67671651a99977391c5552dd90e7bc147308a/buffer/src/main/java/io/netty/buffer/AdaptivePoolingAllocator.java#L112-L120
### Netty version

4.1.115.Final
